the United States of America.

127
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:05,712
Definitely puts Russians ahead
in missing link race.

128
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:07,774
Please advise.

129
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:10,381
Composite picture en route...

130
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:12,252
to Commissar on missing links.

131
00:10:12,311 --> 00:10:14,018
Answer immediately.

132
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,185
This report top-secret.

133
00:10:16,515 --> 00:10:18,893
Repeat. Top-secret.

134
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:31,873
I've just got
a Russian top-secret.

135
00:10:31,931 --> 00:10:34,002
First one of the day.
Good work. What is it?

136
00:10:34,066 --> 00:10:36,205
That's from a Russian trawler
just off our coast.

137
00:10:36,268 --> 00:10:37,611
They radioed Moscow.

138
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:40,014
They found a missing link
in their fishing net.

139
00:10:40,072 --> 00:10:42,052
Claim it's
a scientific breakthrough.

140
00:10:42,108 --> 00:10:44,054
What's this missing link
look like?

141
00:10:44,110 --> 00:10:48,354
Here is a composite we just drew up from
the Russian ship's description of it.

142
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:51,526
I can't imagine...

143
00:10:51,584 --> 00:10:53,291
[bell ringing] what that's
the missing link to.

144
00:10:53,352 --> 00:10:54,888
Just a minute.

145
00:10:58,691 --> 00:11:02,537
Moscow is sending another top-secret
back to the Russian ship.

146
00:11:03,162 --> 00:11:04,436
"Stupid idiots.

147
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:07,706
"From your description,
this is not missing link.

148
00:11:08,234 --> 00:11:11,772
"You have obviously captured
new kind of American spy."

149
00:11:12,438 --> 00:11:14,042
An American spy.

150
00:11:14,206 --> 00:11:18,086
You'd better get this over to the
State Department right away.

151
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:21,420
They won't be back from lunch yet.
It's only 3:00.

152
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:24,552
That's a chance we're going to have to take.
Go on and get over there.

153
00:11:24,617 --> 00:11:26,528
How often do the Russians
capture an American spy?

154
00:11:26,585 --> 00:11:28,929
This is an emergency.
Yes, sir.

155
00:11:37,296 --> 00:11:40,641
Well, Grandpa,
Herman is nowhere to be found.

156
