197
00:13:40,252 --> 00:13:43,790
A <i>SPY?</i>
A <i>SPY?</i>

198
00:13:44,523 --> 00:13:45,695
A <i>SPY?</i>

199
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:48,270
Valeiry, are you sure
of this?

200
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,766
Moscow wired me
this morning.

201
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:53,834
Our missing link
is international spy.

202
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,477
But I not want
to tell you...

203
00:13:56,535 --> 00:14:00,506
until after you finished that
lovely song about the puffer belly.

204
00:14:01,273 --> 00:14:04,049
But I think
there must be some mistake.

205
00:14:04,109 --> 00:14:08,387
If I was an international spy, I think
someone would have let me know.

206
00:14:16,956 --> 00:14:19,197
(Charlie) I've been in the State
Department over 15 years...

207
00:14:19,258 --> 00:14:21,067
and never saw a spy this ugly.

208
00:14:21,126 --> 00:14:24,471
Yeah, Charlie, but you never know what new
gimmick the top brass might have come up with.

209
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:26,009
I guess you're right.

210
00:14:26,065 --> 00:14:29,205
We'd better check it out and see which
department launched this project.

211
00:14:29,268 --> 00:14:31,111
This may be
top-secret stuff.

212
00:14:31,170 --> 00:14:33,343
And that's a classified face,
if I ever saw one.

213
00:14:33,639 --> 00:14:35,084
[phone ringing]

214
00:14:36,742 --> 00:14:39,951
