our glorious leader like this.

239
00:16:02,428 --> 00:16:05,341
By the way, who is our
glorious leader this month?

240
00:16:05,397 --> 00:16:06,774
Never mind.

241
00:16:07,099 --> 00:16:10,672
I know who our glorious leader is.
I was just testing you.

242
00:16:10,736 --> 00:16:14,115
What message should I send to
the fishing boat, Commissar?

243
00:16:14,173 --> 00:16:16,949
To think that Mother Russia
should be embarrassed...

244
00:16:17,009 --> 00:16:19,649
in front of
the whole world like this.

245
00:16:20,612 --> 00:16:23,354
Here is the message
I want you to send:

246
00:16:23,582 --> 00:16:26,995
Whatever you have found,
missing link...

247
00:16:27,686 --> 00:16:29,461
deep-sea creature...

248
00:16:29,621 --> 00:16:32,568
whatever this ugly,
ugly thing is...

249
00:16:33,258 --> 00:16:35,067
do not bring it back.

250
00:16:37,396 --> 00:16:38,670
[clearing throat]

251
00:16:40,265 --> 00:16:42,302
Get rid of it immediately.

252
00:16:42,701 --> 00:16:46,148
Dump it into the ocean or
whatever, but get rid of it.

253
00:16:46,905 --> 00:16:49,181
I have your message,
Commissar.

254
00:16:49,241 --> 00:16:51,050
"Russian Pipe Dream."

255
00:16:51,110 --> 00:16:52,111
[exclaiming]

256
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:56,053
Stroke.

257
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:57,850
Stroke.

258
00:17:00,285 --> 00:17:03,198
Grandpa, do you think
we're doing the right thing?

259
00:17:03,255 --> 00:17:05,360
I tell you, Lily,
this is the only way.

260
00:17:05,424 --> 00:17:07,426
If the State Department
won't help us...

261
00:17:07,493 --> 00:17:09,871
we'll have to rescue
Herman ourselves.

262
00:17:09,928 --> 00:17:11,601
I guess you're right.

263
00:17:11,663 --> 00:17:13,165
But we better hurry.

264
00:17:13,232 --> 00:17:16,179
There's no telling what those
people will do to Herman.

265
00:17:16,235 --> 00:17:18,010
He's so defenseless.

266
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:21,351
Do you think the Russians
will brainwash him?

267
00:17:21,407 --> 00:17:23,546
If they do,
I hope they're careful.

268
00:17:23,609 --> 00:17:26,180
I'd hate to have a son-in-law
with a dishpan brain.

269
00:17:52,638 --> 00:17:53,981
Thank you.

270
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:55,783
Thank you, friends.

271
00:17:55,841 --> 00:17:58,549
You heard the message
from the Commissar?

272
00:17:58,610 --> 00:18:00,248
Herman has got to go.

273
00:18:00,312 --> 00:18:02,417
Yeah, but who's got the heart
to tell him?

274
00:18:02,481 --> 00:18:03,687
(Herman)
Now, ladies and gentleman...

275
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:05,194
I have plan.

276
00:18:05,284 --> 00:18:08,094
We give Comrade Herman
farewell party.

277
00:18:08,854 --> 00:18:09,924
I see.

278
00:18:09,988 --> 00:18:12,764
We kiss him on both cheeks
and then we shoot him.

279
00:18:12,825 --> 00:18:14,327
[speaking Russian]

280
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:18,075
He's too nice guy
for Russki farewell party.

281
00:18:18,664 --> 00:18:22,237
We give him nice, decadent
American farewell party.

282
00:18:23,502 --> 00:18:25,812
Like in MGM musical.

283
00:18:26,505 --> 00:18:30,214
Good, we have much singing,
dancing, laughing.

284
00:18:30,275 --> 00:18:33,916
After that, all of a sudden,
we shuffle him off to Buffalo.

285
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:38,686
(man)
Hey!

286
00:18:38,951 --> 00:18:40,521
[feet stomping]

287
00:18:40,752 --> 00:18:41,753
(man)
Hey!

288
00:18:43,755 --> 00:18:44,790
(man)
Hey!

289
00:18:44,857 --> 00:18:47,963
Listen, Grandpa.
They're torturing poor Herman.

290
00:18:48,260 --> 00:18:50,035
Do you think
he'll be able to hold out?

291
00:18:50,095 --> 00:18:53,076
Don't worry, Lily.
He's got nerves of steel.

292
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:56,841
Yes, but I just hope they
don't rust in this damp air.

293
00:19:00,873 --> 00:19:02,875
N[music playing]

294
00:19:13,252 --> 00:19:16,825
It was a fine idea we give
Herman farewell party, Gregor.

295
00:19:16,889 --> 00:19:19,893
It was only way
we could get him to leave.

296
00:19:27,399 --> 00:19:30,710
It's times like this I'm glad
I'm a Lawrence Welk fan.

297
00:19:31,703 --> 00:19:34,013
Notchey, baby,
you're a gasser.

298
00:19:44,816 --> 00:19:46,796
And I thought
he was in danger.

299
00:19:46,852 --> 00:19:49,492
And what do I find?
Herman-a-go-go.

300
00:19:50,122 --> 00:19:53,103
Lily, maybe
they are there torturing him.

301
00:19:53,158 --> 00:19:57,436
I mean, that's not exactly Juliet
Prowse he's wiggling his watusi with.

302
00:19:58,397 --> 00:20:00,638
Well, I'll put a stop
to that.

303
00:20:43,141 --> 00:20:46,520
They just don't build these
things like they used to.

304
00:20:46,645 --> 00:20:47,885
(Lily)
Herman?

305
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:49,815
(Herman)
Lily.

306
00:20:50,515 --> 00:20:52,051
[stuttering]
And Grandpa.

307
00:20:52,117 --> 00:20:54,620
What are you doing out here
in the middle of the ocean?

308
00:20:54,686 --> 00:20:57,098
That's what
we'd like to ask you.

309
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:01,604
Who are they?

310
00:21:02,427 --> 00:21:04,737
You read
your propaganda booklets.

311
00:21:04,796 --> 00:21:07,640
They're capitalistic tools
of Wall Street.

312
00:21:07,699 --> 00:21:10,043
In the books
they wasn't green.

313
00:21:10,902 --> 00:21:12,779
You know what I think?

314
00:21:12,871 --> 00:21:16,683
I think that you are just
a carousing playboy...

315
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:19,513
and so are all
of your wild friends.

316
00:21:20,646 --> 00:21:23,991
Just playboys.
Playboys! Playboys!

317
00:21:24,049 --> 00:21:26,188
No, Lily,
that one's a girl.

318
00:21:26,551 --> 00:21:28,292
Herman, I'm ashamed of you.

319
00:21:28,353 --> 00:21:30,993
My son-in-law,
the dirty old man.

320
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:36,196
Herman,
you are coming with me.

321
00:21:36,495 --> 00:21:37,838
Yes, dear.

322
00:21:39,698 --> 00:21:43,168
But, lady, we're only having
a little farewell party.

323
00:21:43,268 --> 00:21:45,145
Well, farewell to you.

324
00:21:45,203 --> 00:21:47,979
You just take
your yacht of corruption...

325
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:51,146
and revelry and sail on,
home wreckers.

326
00:21:51,843 --> 00:21:54,585
Don't talk that way
in front of my friends.

327
00:21:55,914 --> 00:21:57,655
Herman, come along.

328
00:22:06,358 --> 00:22:10,431
Well, fellas, Notchey,
goodbye.

329
00:22:10,495 --> 00:22:13,704
If you're ever in Mockingbird
Heights, look me up.

330
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:24,314
That's what Americans
are really like.

331
00:22:25,444 --> 00:22:28,118
Holy mackerel,
what party poopers!

332
00:22:29,047 --> 00:22:30,321
Let's go.

333
00:22:30,615 --> 00:22:32,492
N[music playing]

334
00:22:39,224 --> 00:22:41,568
Lily, won't you
let me explain?

335
00:22:46,131 --> 00:22:47,474
Grandpa...

336
00:22:47,532 --> 00:22:51,810
will you tell that miserable person on
the couch that I am not speaking to him?

337
00:22:52,637 --> 00:22:55,083
Miserable person
on the couch...

338
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:57,586
your wife
is not speaking to you.

339
00:22:57,876 --> 00:22:59,913
You hear that, you fathead?

340
00:22:59,978 --> 00:23:02,288
Please, Grandpa,
just translate.

341
00:23:02,347 --> 00:23:04,793
Never mind
the editorial comment.

342
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:06,996
Even I'm surprised at you.

343
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:11,660
I never thought my dear, sweet,
kind uncle would go ape.

344
00:23:13,792 --> 00:23:17,262
Well, golly-gee. How would you like it
if you were pulled out of the ocean...

345
00:23:17,329 --> 00:23:18,808
in a fishnet
and dumped into a hole...

346
00:23:18,864 --> 00:23:21,936
and have a bunch of people
think you were a missing link?

347
00:23:22,734 --> 00:23:26,580
I tell you that sort of thing is
very damaging to your psyche.

348
00:23:27,005 --> 00:23:28,006
[scoffs]

349
00:23:28,874 --> 00:23:32,287
Why were you carousing
with those people?

350
00:23:32,611 --> 00:23:37,253
Well, Lily, I was just trying to be one
of the boys and friendly and all that.

351
00:23:37,682 --> 00:23:41,721
After all, dear, I am a member of the
Junior Chamber of Commerce, you know.

352
00:23:42,020 --> 00:23:44,125
You've just got
to forgive me.

353
00:23:44,689 --> 00:23:47,329
The way they do on television
every afternoon...

354
00:23:47,392 --> 00:23:49,065
<i>on The Guiding Light.</i>

355
00:23:49,861 --> 00:23:51,067
Go ahead, Lily.

356
00:23:51,129 --> 00:23:54,076
Make up with the big slob
before he starts blubbering...

357
00:23:54,132 --> 00:23:57,602
and washes all the furniture
out into the street again.

358
00:24:01,072 --> 00:24:03,348
Well, all right.

359
00:24:03,642 --> 00:24:05,178
I forgive you.

360
00:24:05,844 --> 00:24:07,448
Thank you, dear.

361
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:10,817
That's real wizard of you.

362
00:24:11,616 --> 00:24:14,961
But I want you to forget about
those Russian friends of yours...

363
00:24:15,020 --> 00:24:18,399
and all of that singing
and dancing and carrying on.

364
00:24:18,557 --> 00:24:21,163
I certainly will, dear.
I promise.

365
00:24:22,027 --> 00:24:23,404
All right.

366
00:24:24,463 --> 00:24:28,070
Now, come on upstairs,
we'd all better get to bed.

367
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,803
I'll be up in a minute,
sweetheart.

368
00:24:32,637 --> 00:24:33,638
[sighs]

369
00:24:54,292 --> 00:24:56,533
♪ Down by the station ♪

370
00:24:56,595 --> 00:24:58,404
♪ Early in the morning ♪

371
00:24:58,463 --> 00:25:00,374
♪ See the little
puffer bellies ♪

372
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:01,968
♪ Standing in a row N'

373
00:25:03,201 --> 00:25:04,202
Hey!

